vulnerability.name: USN-4165-2
vulnerability.description: USN-4165-1 fixed vulnerabilities in Firefox. The update introduced various minor regressions. This update fixes the problems.  We apologize for the inconvenience.  Original advisory details:   Multiple security issues were discovered in Firefox. If a user were  tricked in to opening a specially crafted website, an attacker could  potentially exploit these to cause a denial of service, bypass security  restrictions, bypass same-origin restrictions, conduct cross-site  scripting (XSS) attacks, bypass content security policy (CSP) protections,  or execute arbitrary code.

statements.status_notes: USN-4165-1 caused some minor regressions in Firefox.
